Author: Chad Hazlett, Yiqing Xu, Samuel G.Z. Asher
Maintainer: Samuel G.Z. Asher <sgzasher@stanford.edu>
Description: Provides a general reweighting approach to causal inference with time-series cross-sectional (TSCS) data. It includes two estimators, mean balancing and kernel balancing. The kernel balancing estimator minimizes a kernel maximum mean discrepancy (MMD) objective with entropy regularization to find balancing weights for control units. This approach inherits the ability of synthetic control and latent factor models to tolerate time-varying confounders, while improving feasibility and stability.
